   UIs are built on **screens**, which can be compared to **Android's Activities**.
   Default method implementations are omitted for simplicity.

   @code (language=rust, label=lst:graphics-screen) codes/graphics/screen.txt\
   
   A screen can contain different UIElements, like texts, buttons etc.
   \\
   At startup, the main thread loads the GraphicsManager with all the screen instantiators (initializers).
   The instantiators are summoned when required.

   @code (language=rust, label=lst:graphics-screen-loading) codes/graphics/screen-loading.txt\

   @newpage\

